From your three posts on the WARRIOR board I am quite convinced that you know almost nothing about warriors and apparently not a whole lot about your class.<br>
<br>
AE taunt has a 15 minute refresh time. It only guarantees a sucsessful taunt (putting the warrior 1 hate point ahead of the highest person on the agro list) of the mobs in range. Thats it. It does not guaruntee that the warrior will have agro for the entire 15 minutes between uses.<br>
<br>
Warrior weapons do not fall from the sky like candy. I don't know how many raids I have been to where there will be 3-4 pal/sk uber weapons that drop for the same number of named mobs and not a single warrior weapon. So do not fault the warrior for not having 75k-100k for a fu**ing windblade. Unfortunatly, only the top 1-2% get to be uber. If that includes you, grats to you, but unfortunatly that doesn't include every 60+ warrior that you will encounter.<br>
<br>
I happen to find the voice line spells very useful. Its great for not having to worry about the chanter or shaman getting hit. With it, the SK doesn't have to worry about getting agro and giving it back. The monks and rogues can go all out with dps and not worry about getting hit or turning the mob around just before it enrages.<br>
<br>
As for you soloing, well perhaps that makes you the least qualified to post to this thread. Grouping is about putting your needs aside for the benifit of the group. Not the other way around.<br>
<br>
I agree it is certainly not a perfect group to have a warrior AND a SK or a paladin. Sometimes that is just the way the group happens. <br>
<br>
You give the shadow knight class a bad name. I suppose the rest of your class would be rather put out if all the other classes were to show the snobbery that you have shown and didn't group with SK's just because they don't have very good dps.  <br>
<br>
But then I forgot you are too good to group and you go solo anyway. <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
Half Elven Warlord of 61 Battles<br>
