<br>
I'm generally kinda lazy... my spell line up is as follows<br>
<br>
1-Festering Darkness<br>
2-Banshee Aura<br>
3-Aura of Pain<br>
4-Spear of Plague<br>
5-Harm Shield<br>
6-Mental Corruption<br>
7-Zevfeer's Bite<br>
8-Death Peace<br>
<br>
I don't like swapping out @#%$ hence MC and BA stay memmed 100% of the time. Sometimes Harm Shield comes out for Augmentation of Death (recast on Aug is like 30 seconds, even though it lasts 20+ minutes having to take a 30 second time out to buff Jobaber is annoying). I'm guilty of rarely memming voice for this reason, what I'd LIKE them to do is something like modrod. Mem it, cast it, 0.5 cast time or something similar and then can't cast it again for 10 minutes. (Incidentally I'm missing the highest level Spear and Aura of Hate which'll give me more damage and 2 less spell slots, You'll note I don't even keep a save my ass tap memmed any more. =P)<br>
<br>
With the Spear, AoP, and ZB I'm doing 1200dmg per minute in just nukes and 500 damage per minutes on Festering Darkness. Aggro for me is dirt simple and my spell + pet + melee means my DPS is pretty good too. Yeah, I can give up aggro every fight by FDing but I run at 6400hp (don't have ND3 yet) and 1500ac, generally there isn't too much that's going to hand my ass to me. When it is, I hand over aggro. (Also note that FD is expensive and that using it every fight means I lose mana I could be using for damage).<br>
<br>
My biggest complaint is about warriors that have equipment worse than mine, will fight me for aggro and then not position properly. I mean there are a few to whom I will try to give aggro but can't keep it off the casters. With taunt they manage to keep pulling it off of me and usually into my pet and the pets of other casters. I'd be perfectly happy to let them keep their aggro if they paid any attention at all to the pets.<br>
<br>
Blah, I'm old, I'm jaded, I'm stubborn, maybe using the voice line in exp groups would help the warriors hold aggro better, but honestly... with fungi/Bond of Death/Epic/Dain Ring in a bad situation I can outlive them all, so why bother? (thas 150+ a tic in regen that I can sustain indefinitely as long as I'm not casting anything else) Warriors tank the big nasty @#%$ better, I do better in exp groups and do pretty much jack @#%$ on raids other than summon corpses, they've also taken my fear away and I've found one good solo spot in PoP (and the outter cave in PoV is usually taken.) So I can pull (and pacificism is taking that from me) and I can tank for exp groups, but not anything uber. *shrug* Sue me. <p><font size=5><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=392157">--The Unconscious</a><BR><pre><font color=#000099><font size=2>In your house, I long to be<BR>Room by room, patiently<BR>I'll wait for you there, like a stone<BR>I'll wait for you there, alone</font></pre></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=trysbrinanoqultar464>TrysbrinaNoqultar464</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/2/03 10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2497.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> lol just about all our warriors have EB weapons as well, only 2 dont, 1 is a new and the other stopped playing during velious and just came back.  they have ae taunt as well, but even so all the sks have VoTerris up on a raid and when we get Thule it will be the same as well.  On something like Mithaniel Marr +10% aggro can only help.  and since when did an EB weapon become common enough that