<br>
Additionally, with Voice on the MT, if I hyper aggro a mob and FD/DP it off to the warrior, he pretty much has the mob till one of em is dead.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes I wonder if it's the fact that to use the line, you have to accept a subordinate/secondary role.  I mean, how fun is it to be the 4th or 5th warrior down the line?  I can see how SKs are growing to love their new damage toys.  To some SKs, the benefits to losing the spell slot entirely are very difficult to quantify.  No SK casts it on himself, as he can hold aggro cleanly without it.  Although I do like the catnip analogy, and have seen warriors act similarly with that spell up in xp groups.<br>
<br>
If the warrior isn't positioning correctly, then it's up to the group to get him straight.<br>
