<br>
I think tanks in general tend to be pretty assertive/aggressive.  Its one of the things that makes a good tank.  So its probably pretty common to have people with considerable egos behind the keyboards.<br>
<br>
I've been in groups where the Paladin or Shadow Knight just took it upon themselves to tank.  It wasn't discussed, it wasn't agreed on, they just decided they were tank.  In one case in was probably the right choice, since the Paladin in question was sporting NToV gear while I was in a mishmash of champions and other crap.  In another case I was the one in NToV gear while the SK was in SS and lesser.  In both cases I didn't really have a lot to say about it, since while I might get an occassional taunt to take, they'd just stun/nuke/dot/snare/taunt/whatever it right back.<br>
<br>
In both cases I just went ahead and pulled out my 2hs and let them tank *shrug*.  Obviously it was some kind of power trip for them.  Which many times it is.  If you can't discuss with your group who should tank and why, then you're obviously just into a power trip.  And while I might group with you for the evening, as long as nothing particularly drasitic goes wrong, don't expect me to put you on my friends list or ever want to group with you again.  Being an ass does not win friends or influence people.<br>
<br>
Using inherent abilities of a class that have no relevance what so ever to your abilities as a player as some kind of statement of phallic superiority is pretty retarded, to say the least.  <p>The Man in Black: We are men of action, lies do not become us. <br>
