<br>
The SK community has a well developed sense of persecution complex, forged by the Kunark and Velious expansions (even before the expansions really).<br>
<br>
Today, it's truly a golden age for the class.  Look at the class balance threads, and you see spell stacking and armor tinting as the major concerns of the class.  The class is very complete and extremely viable now -- something that it hasn't been or felt like in well forever really.<br>
<br>
I suspect alot of SKs now revel in their new status as a MT alternative.  After all, the SK is a tank class.  Played by players with the same common makeup as yourselves.<br>
<br>
I'd like to think that SKs generally have the wisdom to see that warriors still are the best pure tanks.  Many (probably most) undoubtedly do.  Some do not.  Either they don't know this, or they do, but choose to ignore this fact.  Considering the historical relationship (or contrast) with warriors specifically, I don't think it's too far of a leap to say many SKs that choose to take aggro, do so out of long standing and misplaced class envy.<br>
<br>
You are probably well served to act as Glatius does. <p>Emmalythe 29th lvl teabagger armswoman (retired)<br>
