As an ancient SK,<br>
<br>
I always politely post my AC and HP with the intention of letting the Cleric and Control peeps decide who tanks.<br>
Usually, the warriors I have met want to tank, but will back down when I outweigh them with HP/AC due to AAXP or equipment, and I willingly do the same if the situation is reversed.<br>
(It is not uncommon for ties to go to the SK when a slower is there, and ties to go to the warrior when unreliable or NO slow is there, but know this, properly AAXP'd SKs are fine tanks for XP groups even in the higher tier planes...)<br>
<br>
Usually, if I am not elected to tank, if the warrior is elected over me, he/she is getting Voice whether he wants it or not. (unless he/she mentions their buff slots are full and that they clicked it as they cant fit it....  I have NEVER had this problem though with warriors)<br>
I like to nuke as much as the next guy, and if a warrior is tanking, every advantage I can give him so we don't get the chanter/cleric beat on is a good thing.<br>
<br>
I don't mind pulling or even playing just *laugh* &quot;damage dealer&quot; or secondary tank, as I usually end up being a chanter or cleric bodyguard...  which most chanters and clerics appreciate to no end. (this is the type of thing that gets you people who will seek you out for a group next time, and gets you free reses and KEI/VoQ.)<br>
<br>
I don't see it as a competition, I see it as a team... and the warrior is part of that team.  As an ancient player, I don't care if the group is perfect, and I'd rather see a good player in my group than the &quot;ideal class&quot; added for the &quot;perfect group&quot;.  I think tanking CAN stack if your ego doesn't get in the way.  As a SK, I can MAKE myself tank at any time...  this does not mean I should all the time...  nor does it mean I should ignore my duties as an intelligent player if a obstinate other &quot;tank&quot; is in the group.<br>
<br>
Teamwork is often harder than solo... <br>
<br>
Warriors place is usually tanking, but that doesn't mean ANY TANK shouldn't be ready to take the secondary role or play damage dealer to the best of their ability.<br>
<br>
Skill is all about know BOTH when to apply an ability and when NOT to.<br>
<br>
P.S. Don't worry about pred, most SKs pay him little heed, especially when he tries to play the &quot;PvP is harder than normal servers&quot; card.<br>
<br>
Baazghul &quot;Brik&quot; Bludgaard<br>
